 LE)\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * so we will break the data up into lines by \\r and/or \\n then if needed we will break each of those into\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * smaller lines to fit within the limit.\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * We will also look for lines that start with a \u0026#39;.\u0026#39; and prepend an additional \u0026#39;.\u0026#39;.\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * NOTE: this does not count towards line-length limit.\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         */\u003c/span\u003e","","        \u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e//Iterate over lines with normalized line breaks\u003c/span\u003e","        \u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\u003c/span\u003elines\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-smi\u003ethis\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e-\u0026gt;\u003cspan class=pl-en\u003eiterateLines\u003c/span\u003e(\u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\u003c/span\u003emsg_data\u003c/span\u003e);","","        \u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e/* To distinguish between a complete RFC822 message and a plain message body, we check if the first field\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * of the first line (\u0026#39;:\u0026#39; separated) does not contain a space then it _should_ be a header, and we will\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         * process all lines before a blank line as headers.\u003c/span\u003e","\u003cspan class=pl-c\u003e         */\u003c/span\u003e","","        \u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\u003c/span\u003efirst_line\u003c/span\u003e = \u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\u003c/span\u003elines\u003c/span\u003e-\u0026gt;\u003cspan class=pl-en\u003ecurrent\u003c/span\u003e();","        \u003cspan class=pl-s1\u003e\u003cspan class=pl-c1\u003e$\